<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1163">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/964a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Consul and Vice
                                    Consul at Nogales, the Consular Agent at Cananea, and the Consul
                                    at Hermosillo</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Say to the Americans who have been supplied with arms for their
                            self-defense that the arms are furnished them solely for the protection
                                <pb facs="0957" n="841" xml:id="pg_841"/> of their lives and that
                            they should most carefully guard against any indiscreet acts; point out
                            the disastrous effects such acts would undoubtedly have upon their own
                            interests and upon the lives and property of Americans elsewhere in
                            Mexico; remind them finally of the responsibility resting upon them in
                            this respect.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>